  "text": "Live cell tracking revealed marked cell-to-cell variability in p21-GFP levels amongst G1 and G2 hTert-RPE1 cells, within the same population (Fig. 1c) . This variability was also seen in hTert-RPE1 cells fixed and immunostained for unlabelled p21 ( Supplementary Fig. 2a ). G1 cells have the highest and most variable p21-GFP levels, and there exists a strong correlation between p21-GFP levels and G1 phase length (R ¼ 0.62**; Fig. 1d ). G2 is associated with lower and less variable p21-GFP levels and correlation between G2 length and p21-GFP levels is weaker than in G1 (R ¼ 0.51**; Supplementary Fig. 2b ). Cells express undetectable levels of p21-GFP during S-phase ( Fig. 1c) , consistent with previous reports 23, [CITATION_1] . We do not observe p21-GFP degradation during mitosis, and mitotic p21-GFP expression does not affect mitotic timing (Supplementary Fig. 2c,d ).",
